flowchart TB
  %% HubSpot Workflow Template
  %% Standard workflow structure with enrollment, branches, and actions

  Start((Workflow Trigger)) --> EnrollmentCheck{Enrollment Criteria Met?}

  EnrollmentCheck -->|No| Exit1((Do Not Enroll))
  EnrollmentCheck -->|Yes| SuppressionCheck{Suppression List Check}

  SuppressionCheck -->|On List| Exit2((Suppressed))
  SuppressionCheck -->|Not On List| Enroll[Enroll Contact]

  Enroll --> Delay1[Delay: 1 day]

  Delay1 --> Branch1{If/Then Branch}

  Branch1 -->|Property = Value| ActionA[Action: Send Email A]
  Branch1 -->|Property != Value| ActionB[Action: Send Email B]

  ActionA --> SetProperty1[Set Property: Status = A]
  ActionB --> SetProperty2[Set Property: Status = B]

  SetProperty1 --> WaitForAction{Wait for: Email Opened}
  SetProperty2 --> WaitForAction

  WaitForAction -->|Opened within 3 days| EngagedPath[Engaged Branch]
  WaitForAction -->|Not opened| NotEngagedPath[Not Engaged Branch]

  EngagedPath --> ActionC[Action: Add to Sales List]
  NotEngagedPath --> Delay2[Delay: 7 days]

  ActionC --> CreateTask[Create Task for Sales Rep]
  Delay2 --> ActionD[Action: Send Reminder Email]

  CreateTask --> UpdateLifecycle[Set Lifecycle Stage: SQL]
  ActionD --> CheckEngagement{Check Engagement Again}

  CheckEngagement -->|Still No Engagement| UnenrollPath[Unenroll: Low Engagement]
  CheckEngagement -->|Now Engaged| EngagedPath

  UpdateLifecycle --> Complete((Workflow Complete))
  UnenrollPath --> Complete
